{"type":"tool_execution_end","toolCallId":"call_0e2d09d32a9d43bfa4468b","toolName":"mcp","result":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C4\ncase_id: arb-ex08-20260630042402\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:1:C4\nremaining_ms: 885657\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex08-20260630042402\",\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"evidence\":[{\"admissibility_status\":\"submitted_evidence\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-30T04:34:28Z\",\"evidence_id\":\"ev_0ed0ef50e84e_submitted-evidence-01-plaintiff-0ed0ef50e84e\",\"mime_type\":\"text/plain\",\"original_name\":\"submitted-evidence-01-plaintiff-0ed0ef50e84e.txt\",\"record_visibility\":\"juror_visible\",\"relevance\":\"Official court source for public release/unsealing. It proves the court granted access to the note and identifies it as a suicide note purportedly authored by Jeffrey Epstein, recovered by Tartaglione, and submitted by Tartaglione attorneys; it also shows the order was about public access, not authenticity.\",\"retrieval_timestamp\":\"2026-06-30T04:33:49Z\",\"sha256\":\"0ed0ef50e84e5f90a63aeefcb840f628038958b10acf229c44b4babea0c133e9\",\"size_bytes\":2992,\"source_description\":\"Official U.S. District Court for the Southern District of New York PDF, Case No. 16-CR-832 (KMK), order dated May 6, 2026; retrieved/rendered for relevant text extraction during this AAR run. Local PDF download succeeded at /aar-codex/sources-20260630-args/sdny-tartaglione-order-2026-05-06.pdf, 128,992 bytes, sha256 7225441cb802084e2b9485ebc2c6d246fbfa08e109fe650cb14f445dc4745ca0; local pdftotext was unavailable.\",\"source_url\":\"https://www.nysd.uscourts.gov/sites/default/files/2026-05/16cr832%20-%20Tartaglione%20Order%20-%2026.5.6.pdf\",\"storage_name\":\"0e/0ed0ef50e84e5f90a63aeefcb840f628038958b10acf229c44b4babea0c133e9\",\"submitted_by_role\":\"plaintiff\",\"submitted_phase\":\"arguments\",\"text_readable\":true,\"title\":\"SDNY May 6, 2026 Tartaglione unsealing order - re