he release to May 6, 2026, and identifies the source as U.S. District Court for the Southern District of New York/Handout via Reuters.\",\"retrieval_timestamp\":\"2026-06-30T04:35:30Z\",\"sha256\":\"58561d19c4537e7f3ade428fefe955b34c55ca688a331faa72187770ee5c8716\",\"size_bytes\":1360,\"source_description\":\"Reuters Connect licensable picture page for image USN RC2T3LAL0C66, byline U.S. District Court/SDNY, retrieved/rendered during this AAR run.\",\"source_url\":\"https://www.reutersconnect.com/item/document-described-as-a-suicide-note-purportedly-written-by-the-late-jeffrey-epstein/dGFnOnJldXRlcnMuY29tLDIwMjY6bmV3c21sX1JDMlQzTEFMMEM2Ng\",\"storage_name\":\"58/58561d19c4537e7f3ade428fefe955b34c55ca688a331faa72187770ee5c8716\",\"submitted_by_role\":\"plaintiff\",\"submitted_phase\":\"arguments\",\"text_readable\":true,\"title\":\"Reuters Connect May 6, 2026 image-caption record for Epstein note\"},{\"admissibility_status\":\"submitted_evidence\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-30T04:38:13Z\",\"evidence_id\":\"ev_5aa56aab2530_submitted-evidence-05-defendant-5aa56aab2530\",\"mime_type\":\"text/plain\",\"original_name\":\"submitted-evidence-05-defendant-5aa56aab2530.txt\",\"record_visibility\":\"juror_visible\",\"relevance\":\"Defense evidence on provenance, custody, and authentication. It reports DOJ's explanation that it never had the note, that the note had not yet been authenticated, that the note came through an unrelated Tartaglione attorney-client dispute, that it was in a court vault since 2021, and that DOJ lawyers involved in sealed proceedings could not disclose anything due to privilege restrictions.\",\"retrieval_timestamp\":\"2026-06-30T04:39:50Z\",\"sha256\":\"5aa56aab25302158d1be6b80426ed4d517ee436cea958297c34e648148db2bca\",\"size_bytes\":2780,\"source_description\":\"Associated Press article by Ed White, retrieved via AP News page during defendant arguments; relevant text extraction from public article page.\",\"source_url\":\"https://apnews.com/article/jef