{"type":"tool_execution_end","toolCallId":"call_927fd86e01a248e09e2aaf","toolName":"mcp","result":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C4\ncase_id: arb-ex08-20260630042402\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:1:C4\nremaining_ms: 863008\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex08-20260630042402\",\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"evidence\":{\"admissibility_status\":\"submitted_evidence\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-30T04:38:13Z\",\"evidence_id\":\"ev_5aa56aab2530_submitted-evidence-05-defendant-5aa56aab2530\",\"mime_type\":\"text/plain\",\"original_name\":\"submitted-evidence-05-defendant-5aa56aab2530.txt\",\"record_visibility\":\"juror_visible\",\"relevance\":\"Defense evidence on provenance, custody, and authentication. It reports DOJ's explanation that it never had the note, that the note had not yet been authenticated, that the note came through an unrelated Tartaglione attorney-client dispute, that it was in a court vault since 2021, and that DOJ lawyers involved in sealed proceedings could not disclose anything due to privilege restrictions.\",\"retrieval_timestamp\":\"2026-06-30T04:39:50Z\",\"sha256\":\"5aa56aab25302158d1be6b80426ed4d517ee436cea958297c34e648148db2bca\",\"size_bytes\":2780,\"source_description\":\"Associated Press article by Ed White, retrieved via AP News page during defendant arguments; relevant text extraction from public article page.\",\"source_url\":\"https://apnews.com/article/jeffrey-epstein-suicide-note-5297f49736e625a06d0db3c7b737b997\",\"storage_name\":\"5a/5aa56aab25302158d1be6b80426ed4d517ee436cea958297c34e648148db2bca\",\"submitted_by_role\":\"defendant\",\"submitted_phase\":\"arguments\",\"text_readable\":true,\"title\":\"AP May 7, 2026 report: DOJ seeing Epstein note for first time and authentication limits\"},\"limits\":{\"max_read_bytes\":65536,\"max_read_bytes_per_opportunity\":524288,\"max_reads_per_opportunity\":32,\"remaining_read_bytes_for_opportunity\":515370,\"remaining_reads_for_opportunity\":28}},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":false,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-30T05:02:11.941771357Z\",\"deliberation_round\":1,\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:1:C4\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":863008,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":12}}"}],"details":{"mode":"call","mcpResult":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C4\ncase_id: arb-ex08-20260630042402\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:1:C4\nremaining_ms: 863008\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex08-20260630042402\",\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"evidence\":{\"admissibility_status\":\"submitted_evidence\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-30T04:38:13Z\",\"evidence_id\":\"ev_5aa56aab2530_submitted-evidence-05-defendant-5aa56aab2530\",\"mime_type\":\"text/plain\",\"original_name\":\"submitted-evidence-05-defendant-5aa56aab2530.txt\",\"record_visibility\":\"juror_visible\",\"relevance\":\"Defense evidence on provenance, custody, and authentication. It reports DOJ's explanation that it never had the note, that the note had not yet been authenticated, that the note came through an unrelated Tartaglione attorney-client dispute, that it was in a court vault since 2021, and that DOJ lawyers involved in sealed proceedings could not disclose anything due to privilege restrictions.\",\"retrieval_timestamp\":\"2026-06-30T04:39:50Z\",\"sha256\":\"5aa56aab25302158d1be6b80426ed4d517ee436cea958297c34e648148db2bca\",\"size_bytes\":2780,\"source_description\":\"Associated Press article by Ed White, retrieved via AP News page during defendant arguments; relevant text extraction from public article page.\",\"source_url\":\"https://apnews.com/article/jeffrey-epstein-suicide-note-5297f49736e625a06d0db3c7b737b997\",\"storage_name\":\"5a/5aa56aab25302158d1be6b80426ed4d517ee436cea958297c34e648148db2bca\",\"submitted_by_role\":\"defendant\",\"submitted_phase\":\"arguments\",\"text_readabl